{
  "id": "ex_technical_abba4760",
  "intent": "Execute mass spectrometry sample preparation protocol involving antibody spotting followed by sample incubation. First, dispense 1.5\u00b5L of each antibody onto designated slide wells using p20 pipette, incubate overnight at 4\u00b0C, then perform sequential washes with detergent wash buffer (250\u00b5L), BSA blocking buffer (250\u00b5L), PBS (2x 250\u00b5L), and water (250\u00b5L). After desiccation, distribute 100\u00b5L of each serum sample in duplicate across slide wells using p300 pipette, incubate for 2 hours at room temperature with shaking, then complete final wash sequence with PBS (2x 250\u00b5L) and water (2x 250\u00b5L).",
